---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { url } from '../../lib/url';
import { commands } from '../../data/commands';

const title = 'Commands';
const description =
  'Nine commands for the highest-leverage moves in context engineering. Bootstrap, audit, document, plan, decide, scope, secure, verify, onboard.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="container container--wide commands-index">
    <h1>Nine commands. One job each.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Each command lives in its own file in the skill. Each one is a procedure
      the agent runs literally, not a vibe. Click through for the
      <em>why</em>, the <em>when</em>, and the <em>what it produces</em>.
    </p>

    <table class="cmd-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Command</th>
          <th>What it does</th>
          <th>Reach for it when</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {commands.map((c) => (
          <tr>
            <td>
              <a class="cmd-link" href={url(`commands/${c.slug}/`)}>
                <code>{c.name}</code>
                <span class="cmd-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              </a>
            </td>
            <td class="cmd-cell-line">{c.oneLiner}</td>
            <td class="cmd-cell-reach">{c.reachFor}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <section class="bundle">
      <h2>How the commands fit together</h2>
      <p>
        The commands are independent. Pick the one you need. There is also a
        natural lifecycle:
      </p>
      <ol class="bundle-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Start</strong> with <a href={url('commands/init/')}><code>init</code></a>
          (new repo) or <a href={url('commands/document/')}><code>document</code></a>
          (existing repo with stale context).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Wire verification</strong> with
          <a href={url('commands/verify/')}><code>verify</code></a>. This is the
          single highest-leverage move. Do not skip it.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Capture decisions</strong> with
          <a href={url('commands/adr/')}><code>adr</code></a> as they happen.
          Before any non-trivial change, draft a contract with
          <a href={url('commands/plan/')}><code>plan</code></a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Refine</strong> with <a href={url('commands/scope/')}><code>scope</code></a>
          (multi-stack repos), <a href={url('commands/mcp/')}><code>mcp</code></a>
          (before connecting an agent to production), and
          <a href={url('commands/onboard/')}><code>onboard</code></a> (fresh
          session, fresh teammate).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Check yourself</strong> with
          <a href={url('commands/audit/')}><code>audit</code></a> on a
          cadence. Quarterly is enough.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="related">
      <h2>The model underneath</h2>
      <p>
        Every command is built on a small shared vocabulary: five context
        layers, a five-stage lifecycle, the kinds of debt AI accelerates, and
        the anti-patterns to reject. If you have not read
        <a href={url('foundation/')}>the foundation</a> yet, that is the right
        first stop. Five short pages.
      </p>
      <p>
        The source material, <em>The 2026 Context Engineering Blueprint</em>,
        is reproduced in full at <a href={url('blueprint/')}>/blueprint</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .cmd-table {
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .cmd-table td { padding: 1rem 0.6rem; }
    .cmd-link {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-weight: 650;
    }
    .cmd-link code {
      background: none;
      border: none;
      padding: 0;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    .cmd-link:hover { color: var(--ember-ink); }
    .cmd-link:hover .cmd-arrow { color: var(--ember); transform: translateX(2px); }
    .cmd-arrow {
      color: var(--muted);
      transition: transform 120ms ease, color 120ms ease;
    }
    .cmd-cell-line { color: var(--ink-soft); }
    .cmd-cell-reach { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.93rem; }

    .bundle {
      margin-top: 4rem;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: var(--bg-soft);
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 12px;
    }
    .bundle h2 { margin-top: 0; }
    .bundle-list { line-height: 1.7; }
    .bundle-list li { margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }

    .related { margin-top: 4rem; }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .cmd-table { font-size: 0.9rem; }
      .cmd-cell-reach { display: none; }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
